  "prompt": "What are the competitive exams that you can give during 4 years of engineering?",
  "response": "During your 4-year engineering degree, you can appear for several competitive exams:\n\n1. For Higher Studies:\n- GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering)\n- GRE (Graduate Record Examination)\n- CAT (Common Admission Test)\n- MAT (Management Aptitude Test)\n- GMAT (Graduate Management Admission Test)\n\n2. For Government/PSU Jobs:\n- ISRO Scientist/Engineer Exam\n- DRDO Exam\n- SSC Engineering Services Exam\n- UPSC Engineering Services Exam\n- BHEL Exam\n- ONGC Exam\n\n3. For Technical Jobs:\n- TCS NQT (National Qualifier Test)\n- Infosys Placement Exam\n- Wipro WILP\n- AMCAT\n- IBM Talent Management Test\n\n4. Technical Certification Exams:\n- Microsoft Certification\n- Cisco Certification\n- Oracle Certification\n- Red Hat Certification\n- AWS Certification\n\n5. Competitive Programming:\n- Google Code Jam\n- ACM ICPC\n- Hackathons\n- Coding Competitions\n\n6. Other Competitive Exams:\n- JAM (Joint Admission Test)\n- CSIR-NET\n- IOCL Exam\n\nPreparing for these exams alongside your engineering curriculum can enhance your career prospects.",
